title: Black Sabbath  1994-02-08  New Britain, CT USA (SBD) FLAC
description:
Black Sabbath February 8, 1994
The Sting - New Britain, CT


Transfer info:
Master> HD> FLAC 6> FTP> Make torrent2> you!

This is a Soundboard recording of the 1st night of the mighty Sabbath's "Cross Purposes" tour. It is complete except for the encore which was "Sabbath Bloody Sabbath".

While available as silver boot press, these files were made from the master that was used to produce the silver, so I thought I'd post them. My source has asked to remain nameless. 

This was an informal ftp trade, so I don't know how it was transferred to HD, but the rest of the lineage info is completely accurate. There were no ffp files so I created some. Sorry if this has already been here or if there is something left out. I don't upload much. I have a pretty large Sabbath collection and am thinking of upping some of the gems that I have. 

There is no artwork for this particular version, but the artwork for the silver version is up at sabbathlive.com
